      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Leafs",
        "body": "The Toronto Maple Leafs blew a 3-0 first-period lead Monday night, handing Dallas a 6-5 gut-punch that slammed the door on their home schedule and any lingering whispers of dignity in this lost season&mdash;their first playoff miss since 2016.[1][4] Sitting dead last in the Atlantic with a dismal 32-35-14 record and 78 points through 81 games, they've cratered under Craig Berube, who at least had the grace to call the fans \"fabulous\" amid the wreckage, a nod to the loyalists who deserve better than this collapse.[1] No one's hotter than recalled netminder Dennis Hildeby, yanked up from the Marlies for tonight's curtain call, while Archy Tiamov heads down and prospect Landon Sim inks a two-year ELC&mdash;small sparks in a franchise reeling from Brad Treliving's firing.[3] The ghosts of squandered potential haunt Scotiabank Arena, from Matthews' invisible stretches to a blue line that folded like cheap tin. But change brews: off-season housecleaning looms, Berube's seat scorching. <strong>Watch the finale tonight in Ottawa</strong>&mdash;win or lose, it's the appetizer for a summer of reckoning that could redefine this dinosaur or bury it for good.<strong>[1][3]</strong>",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
